commit.message: remove extra carriage returns

fix possible buffer overflow in get_path

If a pathname is longer than CFG_MAX_FILENAME, there was a possible
buffer overflow when copying the path name.
release dot.conf 1.3

update the dotconf features document

Explain environment variable substitution in greater detail and update
the description of the include facility.

Signed-off-by: William Hubbs <w.d.hubbs@gmail.com>

removed extern "c" declaration from private header file

This is not needed since dotconf is written in c.

fix include path processing

In dotconf_create, if DC_INCLUDEPATH is not set, set the default for
includepath to be the same directory where the configuration file is
located if possible.  This makes much more sense than using the current
working directory as the default for include files.

If this cannot be done, includepath is left empty by default.
release dotconf 1.2

Remove wildcards from examples/Makefile.am.

We need to do this for make distcheck.  It chokes on filenames with
wildcards.  These haven't posed problems for any of the other targets,
including make dist.  It is baffling.

Signed-off-by: William Hubbs <w.d.hubbs@gmail.com>

solaris fix

The -Wall flag only works for gcc, but I found other similar flags in
the opentts code base, thanks to Willie Walker.
typeo fix in src/Makefile.am
remove unnecessary check for libdl
small update to readme

do not print context pointer in duplicates example

The original duplicates example was printing the context pointers which
was causing the test to fail, and is not necessary to illustrate the
feature.

fix build order in maketest.sh

We need to be sure that libpool is built before the tests that need it
are run.
fixed context example to not use dotconf-config

fix "modules" example

The modules test was relying on the $USER environment variable as part
of the output.  This insured that this test would fail unless the USER
environment variable was set to lukas.  The fix was to use a different
environment variable, "TESTUSER" which is set to"lukas" inside the
program and retrieved when the config file is processed.
convert exit calls in examples/context and examples/duplicate to return
make examples/maketest.sh executable

moved doc/examples to examples in source tree

This is only a source tree change; it does not affect the installation
location for the examples.

remove test suite output from repository

The file named "testoutput" in each example directory is generated when
the tests are run, so it does not belong in the repository.  I have
removed it and added an ignore pattern so that it will not be re-added.

removed the .spec file

I feel that this file should be maintained separately by the packager.
If anyone disagrees, let me know and I'll consider adding it back to
this repository.
install examples under docdir/examples
move examples to doc directory
remove unneeded messages from configure.ac
install documentation

Revert "install documentation and examples"

This reverts commit 64085cdf4e12c3e8b8b630d88fd7df173c6e6b75.

install documentation and examples

The examples have been moved under the doc directory and added to the
list of files to install.

documentation updates

I fixed some typos and documented the dvalue field in the command_t
structure.
updated ignore patterns

hide internal utility functions

Several utility functions which were used internally were in the public
header file.  These have been moved to a private header file which will
not be installed on users systems.
